      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BEV'S NINE (1) remains undefeated in four runs and looks well placed for this. Ploughed through the heavy (8) going first-up with a comprehensive win over 1100m at Rosehill in this class. Kept up to the mark with a 900m trial placing. Can stalk the good tempo and finish over the top of these. KIMBERLEY SECRETS (4) kept fresh when she sat on the strong tempo as fav for a sharp win over 1100m at this track last Friday. Up in class but hard to ignore in this rich vein of form. Each way. SHALAA GOLD (6) gets a better set-up tonight at her third run back and best form is over this track and trip. Winning rider hops back aboard and the cross over nose band comes off from the low draw. Value prospect. JAEGERS (8) smart filly resuming. Nailed late by the progressive Cinsault with a tough second over 1200m at this track last December. Wasn't pushed out in her only trial and gets her chance on the limit.",
